Project:
- program name: lxe
- purpose: Limited two-pass SIC/XE assembler.
- inputs: one or more assembler source files passed via command line.
- outputs per input
  - <name>.l listing file
  - <name>.st symbol table file

Class and assignment information:
- Class: CS530
- Assignment: Project 2, a limited XE assembler

File manifest:
- main.cpp
- assembler_types.h
- parser.h, parser.cpp
- optab.h, optab.cpp
- symtab.h, symtab.cpp
- pass1.h, pass1.cpp
- pass2.h, pass2.cpp
- listing.h, listing.cpp
- Makefile
- README
- Assignment.txt
- reference/*
- sample/*

Compiling instructions:
1) Run: make
2) Executable created: ./lxe

usage instructions:
- Run with 1 or more files:
  ./lxe file1.sic [file2.sic ...]
- If no arguments are provided, lxe prints a message and exits.

design decisions:
- Two-pass pipeline:
  - Pass 1 computes addresses and builds symbol table.
  - Pass 2 resolves symbols and emits object code for listing lines.
- optab is a static in-memory table for SIC/XE opcodes and valid formats
- parser supports label/opcode/operand/comment fields and addressing markers
  (+, `#`, @, ,X) in source text.

Extra features:
- Multi file invocation in one run.
- Basic error reporting for duplicate symbols, unknown opcodes, and range failures

Known bugs / things to imrpove:
- This initial version does not implement directives outside assignment scope
  (EQU/ORG/LTORG/EXTDEF/EXTREF/CSECT)
- Literal pools are not assembled in this version.
- Listing column format may need final alignment tuning to exactly match Canvas.

